<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  AYONAE RO - The Maestra</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_ayonae.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Demi-Goddess of Music, created by Druzzil Ro, the Matron of the Art.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  DRUZZIL RO - Matron of the Art</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_druzzilro.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Goddess of Magic, able to change her form and that of her Plane at will. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  LUCLIN - The Maiden of Shadows</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_luclin.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Seeded life on the moon of Luclin while the other gods and demi-gods squabbled over the lands of Norrath<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  MORELL THULE - The Lord of Dreams</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_morrell_thule.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Creates Dreams and the creatures of Night-visions<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> TERRIS THULE - The Dream Scorcher</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_terris_thule.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
The opposite of Morell Thule, she creates nightmares and the creatures of them. She's also frigging ugly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  SARYRN - The Mistress of Torment</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_saryrn.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Once a beautiful human maiden, at some point she was chosen to rise to the sides of the gods as the Demi-Goddess of pain.  Randomly chooses victims from any plane or dimension and subjects them to unimaginable levels of torture.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Tallon Zek and Vallon Zek - The Beholder of Battle and the Governor of War</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_tallon_zek.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_vallonzek.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Actually two personalities within the same being, they are the masters of Tactics and Strategy and aid their father Rallos Zek in conjuring brilliant plans for war.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  VAZAELLE KALEINE - The Mad</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_vazaelle.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
A devout follower of Cazic Thule, driven insane by visions of fear and destruction.  She was lifted up by him and given her own domain, and from there she touches the lives of random souls, driving them completely insane.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  ZEBUXORUK - The Forsaken</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/library/images/d_zebuxoruk.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Not truly a planar being, and yet a god.  Not really an immortal, and yet ever-living.  Zebuxoruk is everything and nothing; essentially he just plain doesn't fit in.  There's no category which can really be applied to him.  He is known to give power to people and individuals who have lost their path in the way of the universe and have nothing to turn to.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  XEV BRISTLEBANE - The Prince of Fortune</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
((No image available))<br>
Twin brother of Fizzlethorpe Bristlebane, the King of Thieves.  All good fortune in life is due to the benevolent heart of the kind ruler of the demi-plane of Fortune.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  LANYS T'VYL - The Envious Maiden</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
((No Image Available))<br>
The daughter of Innoruuk, given her own domain by her father when she was killed in a final stand-off with the Knight of Tunare, Firiona Vie.  Her domain reflected the jealousy she felt for the power of Firiona in her last moments of life.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  FIRIONA VIE - The Princess of Life</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
((No image available))<br>
Born a Koada'Dal Princess, she was recognized by Tunare for her... ugh... pure heart at a young age.  She used to have a somewhat interesting storyline played out by EQ's Quest Troupe,  and it was usually what led to the various discoveries and expansions of Norrath.  Around a year ago, it seems that Verant decided to forget all of that and use her only as the sex symbol to sell EQ boxes.<br>
<br>
